james h gildea a democrat who represented 
pennsylvania in the us house from 1935 to 1939 died sunday of 
cardiac arrest at age 97 
gildea who died at the manor care nursing home in arlington was 
a native of coaldale pa he made his home in bethesda md before 
entering manor care four years ago 
he was elected to congress in 1934 and reelected two years 
later he was defeated by a gop opponent in 1938 and also was 
defeated in house races in 1940 and 1950 
gildea had become a printing apprentice in 1905 and a newspaper 
publisher in 1910 he founded the coaldale observer a weekly 
newspaper and the schuylkill legal record a law publication 
survivors include his wife genevieve of bethesda 
