<TEXT>
a strong earthquake triggered 
landslides shattered windows and caused power blackouts in the 
lower half of new zealands south island on saturday officials said 
the quake measured 65 on the richter scale but damage was 
limited because the quake was centered on the sparselypopulated 
area of lake te anau north of the town of invercargill officials 
said 
there were no immedate reports of injuries 
murray lowry of the wellington seismological observatory said 
sunday that aftershocks could be expected to continue for as long as 
a month 
the richter scale measures ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude thus a reading of 75 reflects an earthquake 10 times 
stronger than one of 65 
an earthquake of 60 on the richter scale can cause severe damage 
and a 70 reading is a major earthquake capable of widespread 
heavy damage 
</TEXT>
