<TEXT>
the worlds leading industrialized democracies 
have held annual economic summits since 1975 when leaders first 
gathered for informal talks at rambouillet near paris 
the original six participants were the united states japan west 
germany france britain and italy canada joined the group in 1976 
and the european economic community was invited to participate in 
1977 
summit sites rotate among member nations meetings have been held 
in puerto rico 1976 london 1977 bonn 1978 tokyo 1979 venice 
1980 ottawa and montebello 1981 versailles 1982 williamsburg 
1983 london 1984 bonn 1985 tokyo 1986 and venice 1987 
</TEXT>
