<TEXT>
three years ago larry bell set out to 
grab a share of the retail beer market a very small share 
bell owns one of a growing number of microbrewers small 
companies that make small amounts of beer mostly heavier brews 
sales doubled last year and bell 29 hopes his kalamazoo 
brewery will break even or even turn a profit this year 
he began his business on 39000 borrowed from friends in a 
former plumbing supply store with a 15gallon pot and stove while 
business has picked up a bit everything still is done by hand 
bell once said his brewery was the smallest in the country he 
now produces about 1400 barrels of ale annually which may bring in 
about 250000 in sales this year mushrooming from the 65000 in 
sales last year 
the association of brewers estimates there are 80 microbreweries 
nationwide up from 46 two years ago some speculate that the 
popularity of the breweries increased as people began looking for 
alternatives to light highly carbonated us beers 
despite the growth of these small operations major brewers 
arent foaming about competition last year less than 01 percent 
of the 187 million barrels of beer were consumed in the united 
states came from small brewers 
thats not a number that one takes very seriously said jerry 
steinman publisher of the beer marketers insight newsletter it 
would take tremendous growth before the microbreweries have any 
effect on the industry 
one of the big problems for little breweries is delivery beer 
that isnt pasteurized goes bad without refrigeration a problem 
that drove chelsea brewing co of ann arbor mich out of business 
several years ago 
the failure rate for small breweries is pretty high said jeff 
mendel administrator of the institute for fermentation and brewing 
in boulder colo 
about one brewery in five closes down he said some last 
four or five years and some close in a matter of weeks 
meantime bell keeps pumping out his brew with an eye toward some 
mechanization he bought a bottling machine but it is in need of 
repair he hopes to raise another 100000 for more equipment 
its very difficult to make money when youre washing bottles 
by hand he said were just starting to get to the breakeven 
point but its been a real crap shoot 
</TEXT>
